reference.Refstring: Natt och Dag, J., Regnell, B., Carlshamre, P., Andersson, M., & Karlsson, J. (2002). A feasibility study of automated natural language requirements analysis in market-driven development. Requirements Engineering, 7(1), 20-33.

descriptions.definition: "A requirement may be similar to another to the extent that it is regarded as a duplicate and thus eliminated."
descriptions.impact: "The duplicates are important to find to avoid doing the same job twice, assigning the same requirement to different developers, or getting two solutions to the same problem."
